parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to accidents, stranding, or inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: shows empty when the tank is full
or shows full when the tank is empty. The low fuel warning light may come on even when the tank is not empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring to the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
and the fuel pump fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to unexpected running out of fuel, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: and the fuel level sensor fails to transmit accurate information to the fuel gauge.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Power Window and Door Lock Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the power windows and door locks to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: windows hesitating to go up or down
and smoke or sparks from the door module.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight Failure (Low Beam and Daytime Running Lights)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the Stabilitrak system can cause loss of power and reduced vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight Failure (Low Beam and Daytime Running Lamps)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the low beam headlights and daytime running lamps can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The low beam headlights and daytime running lamps fail to illuminate
or intermittently shut off and on
sometimes requiring the use of high beams to drive safely.
